'''Donald P. Tashkin''' is an American [[pulmonology|pulmonologist]]<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/25/AR2006052501729.html|author= Marc Kaufman|title=Study Finds No Cancer-Marijuana Connection|publisher=[[The Washington Post]]|date=May 26, 2006|accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref> and professor of medicine at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]],<ref name=time>{{cite web|url=http://healthland.time.com/2012/01/10/study-smoking-marijuana-not-linked-with-lung-damage/|title=Study: Smoking Marijuana Not Linked with Lung Damage|work=Time|date=January 10, 2012|accessdate= September 26, 2015|author=Szalavitz, Maia}}</ref> who has studied the effects of [[cannabis (drug)|cannabis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lung.med.ucla.edu/faculty/tashkin.htm |title=Donald P. Tashkin, M.D. |publisher=[[University of California, Los Angeles]] |accessdate=October 10, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131010143712/http://www.lung.med.ucla.edu/faculty/tashkin.htm |archivedate=October 10, 2013 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> 

==Career==
Tashkin has spent 30 years studying cannabis.<ref>{{cite news|title=There Seems to Be No Link between Marijuana Use and Lung Cancer|url=http://archive.news.softpedia.com/news/There-Seems-to-Be-No-Link-between-Marijuana-Use-and-Lung-Cancer-24575.shtml|date=May 24, 2006|accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref> In 2006, he was in charge of a large case-control study on marijuana and the risk of cancer. Contrary to his group's expectations, the study found no increase in lung cancer risk even among heavy users of marijuana.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://norml.org/news/2009/06/18/feds-top-pot-researcher-says-marijuana-should-be-legal|title=Feds' Top Pot Researcher Says Marijuana Should Be Legal|publisher=The National Organization for the Reform of Marijuana Laws|date=June 18, 2009|accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://patients4medicalmarijuana.wordpress.com/category/donald-tashkin/|title=Media Ignored Expert’s Shocking Findings That Marijuana Helps Prevent Lung Cancer: Now It’s Med-School Material |publisher=Patients for Medical Cannabis|accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/large-study-finds-no-link/|title=Large Study Finds No Link between Marijuana and Lung Cancer|work=Scientific American|date=May 25, 2006|accessdate=March 20, 2016|author=Biello, David}}</ref>

