{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}} The '''gas leak phone call scam''' was a series of incidents in 2016. The incidents involve a person [[prank call]]ing a restaurant, claiming to be a fire department official and then convincing managers to break all the windows to prevent a [[gas explosion]] occurring due a supposed [[gas leak]]. The calls have been most often placed at [[fast food restaurant]]s in the [[United States]].
==Incidents== A caller who identifies themselves as a [[firefighter]] or other [[authority figure]] contacts a manager or supervisor and would solicit their help in combating a gas leak at the restaurant by breaking all the windows causing thousands of dollars in damages to the establishment.<ref>{{cite news|first=Yanan|last=Wang|title=A weird hoax prompts fast food workers in 3 states to suddenly smash restaurant windows|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/04/11/a-caller-tells-minn-fast-food-workers-break-the-windows-of-your-restaurant-right-now/|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=April 11, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2016}}</ref>
Some notable incidents were: *Two calls were reported on January 30, 2016: one at a [[Wendy's]] restaurant in [[Phoenix, Arizona]] and a [[Burger King]] restaurant in [[Morro Bay, California]].<ref>{{cite news|title=PD: Wendy's manager told to break all of the windows in phone hoax|url=http://www.abc15.com/news/region-phoenix-metro/central-phoenix/pd-wendys-manager-told-to-break-all-of-the-windows-in-phone-hoax|work=[[KNXV-TV]]|date=February 4, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Danielle|last=Ames|title=Burger King employees break windows after prank call about gas leak, Morro Bay police say|url=http://www.sanluisobispo.com/news/local/article57632268.html|newspaper=[[The Tribune (San Luis Obispo)|The Tribune]]|date=January 31, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2016}}</ref> *On February 2, 2016 a [[Jack in the Box]] restaurant in [[Tucson, Arizona]].<ref>{{cite news|first1=Ally|last1=Aldrete|first2=Jennifer|last2=Delacruz|title=Prank call leads to fast-food employees smashing windows|url=http://www.kgun9.com/news/local-news/prank-call-leads-to-fast-food-employees-smashing-windows|work=[[KGUN-TV]]|date=February 3, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2016}}</ref> *On April 7, 2016, a Burger King restaurant in [[Shawnee, Oklahoma]] where workers were told to break the windows due to build-up of [[carbon monoxide]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Kristen|last=Shanahan|title=Employees at Oklahoma Burger King bust out windows after prank call|url=http://kfor.com/2016/04/08/employees-at-oklahoma-burger-king-bust-out-windows-after-prank-call/|work=[[KFOR-TV]]|date=April 8, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2016}}</ref> *On April 8, 2016, a Burger King restaurant in [[Coon Rapids, Minnesota]].<ref>{{cite news|first=James|last=Walsh|title=Prank caller leads Coon Rapids Burger King employees to smash their windows|url=http://www.startribune.com/coon-rapids-burger-king-employees-smash-windows-after-prank-call/375133871/|newspaper=[[Star Tribune]]|date=April 9, 2016|accessdate=April 11, 2016}}</ref> *On April 10, 2016, a Jack in the Box restaurant in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Matt|last=Adams|title=Indy Jack in the Box latest to fall prey to fast food ‘gas leak’ prank|url=http://fox59.com/2016/04/12/indy-jack-in-the-box-latest-to-fall-prey-to-fast-food-gas-leak-prank/|work=[[WXIN|Fox59]]|date=April 12, 2016|accessdate=April 12, 2016}}</ref>
