{{short description|Belgian singer}} {{Update|date=March 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2010}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Kim Kay | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = Kim Van Hee | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1978|2|22|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Dendermonde]], [[Belgium]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | other_names = | instrument = | genre = [[Eurodance]] | occupation = Singer | years_active = 1998–2004, 2015–present | label = [[EMI]] }} '''Kim Kay''' ([[pseudonym]] of '''Kim Van Hee'''; born in [[Dendermonde]], 22 February 1978) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] pop [[singer]]. She is [[Flemish people|Flemish]], however she's known for delivering vocals in French. Kim Kay's arguably most famous work is her dance single "[[Lilali]]", which was a hit in Europe, beyond Belgium and France, where she booked her overall greatest successes throughout her career.
Kay lives in [[Wichelen]] and studies psychology in [[Ghent]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sites.zonien.be/chris_vandenabeele/selektie/2002/selek2002a.htm |last=Vandenabeele |first=Chris |title=Kim Kay - "The Sun Shines" |work=Eurosong - The Belgian Preselection 2002 |publisher=Belgian Eurovision Union |date=20 January 2002 |access-date=10 February 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090814030401/http://sites.zonien.be/chris_vandenabeele/selektie/2002/selek2002a.htm |archivedate=14 August 2009 |df= }}</ref> In 2004, she was diagnosed with [[cervical cancer]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kim Kay heeft kanker|publisher=Nieuwsblad|date=26 November 2004|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/Article/Detail.aspx?articleID=ge0ah0eq|access-date=10 February 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/944/Celebrities/article/detail/1074896/2010/03/03/Kim-Kay-vecht-tegen-morfineverslaving.dhtml|title=Kim'Kay vecht tegen morfineverslaving|date=3 March 2010|publisher=HLN.be|access-date=13 July 2016|language=Dutch|trans-title=Kim'Kay fighting morphine addiction}}</ref>
