{{Infobox writer | name = Lenka Procházková | embed = | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = Lenka Procházková 2015.jpg | image_size = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = Lenka Procházková, 2015 | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1951|3|24}} | birth_place = [[Olomouc]], [[Czechoslovakia]] | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = | residence = | nationality = [[Czechs|Czech]] | citizenship = [[Czech Republic]] | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | partner = [[Ludvík Vaculík]] | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = {{URL|lenka-prochazkova.eu}} | portaldisp = }} '''Lenka Procházková''' (born March 24, 1951) is a [[Czechs|Czech]] writer.<ref name=portal>{{cite web |url=http://www.czechlit.cz/en/authors/prochazkova-lenka/ |title=Lenka Procházková |work=Czech literary portal}}</ref>
The daughter of writer [[Jan Procházka (writer)|Jan Procházka]], she was born in [[Olomouc]], grew up in [[Prague]] and studied journalism and cultural theory at [[Charles University in Prague]]. Procházková signed [[Charter 77]] and, as a result, was forced to work as a manual labourer until 1989. She was later employed in various social and cultural agencies. She also taught at [[Josef Škvorecký]]’s Literary Academy.<ref name=portal/> She had a long-time partnership with writer [[Ludvík Vaculík]], with whom she had two sons.<ref name=miller>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=Y-TMhtk5AUYC&pg=PA263 |title=Who's who in Contemporary Women's Writing |page=263 |last=Miller |first=Jane Eldridge |year=2001 |ISBN=0415159806}}</ref>
In 1982, she received the Egon Hostovský Prize.<ref name=portal/>
Procházková published her first novel ''Růžová dáma'' (The Pink Lady) in 1982. She has also written radio plays and scripts for television. With lawyer [[Aleš Pejchal]], she hosted a program on [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|Radio Free Europe]].<ref name=miller/>
Her sister [[Iva Procházková|Iva]] is also a novelist.<ref name=portal/>
== Works<ref name=miller/> == * ''Oční kapky'' (Eye Drops), novel (1987) * ''Hlídač holubů'' (Pigeon Guard), short stories (1987) * ''Smolná kniha'' (Doomsday book), novel (1991) * ''Zvrhlé dny'' (Perverse days), short stories (1995) * ''Pan ministr'' (Mr. Minister), historical work (1996) * ''Beránek'' [The Lamb], novel (2000)<ref name=portal/>
